&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Anduril Industries is a defense technology company with a mission to transform U.S. and allied military capabilities with advanced technology. By bringing the expertise, technology, and business model of the 21st century’s most innovative companies to the defense industry, Anduril is changing how military systems are designed, built and sold. Anduril’s family of systems is powered by Lattice OS, an AI-powered operating system that turns thousands of data streams into a realtime, 3D command and control center. As the world enters an era of strategic competition, Anduril is committed to bringing cutting-edge autonomy, AI, computer vision, sensor fusion, and networking technology to the military in months, not years.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Anduril Cyber is positioning Anduril as the leading provider of expeditionary cyber capabilities. As a new business line at Anduril, we are pioneering the integration of Anduril&#39;s autonomous vehicles, mesh networks, and electronic warfare products to conduct cyber operations at the edge. We design and build innovative solutions to conduct cyber operations in unconventional or difficult to reach environments.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Mission Software Engineering team builds, deploys, integrates, extends, and scales Anduril&#39;s software to deliver mission-critical capabilities to our customers. As the team closest to Anduril customers and end-users, Mission Software Engineers own the end-to-end buildout and delivery of exceptional software capabilities that meet the customer&#39;s mission.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE JOB&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As a Front End Software Engineer, you will work closely with end-users, Product and Design teams, and backend engineering teams to create intuitive and effective User Experiences that bring Lattice OS to the customer’s mission. Your efforts will ensure that Anduril products are usable and mission-capable. Above all, Mission Software Engineers are driven by a “Whatever It Takes” mindset—executing in an expedient, scalable, and pragmatic way while keeping the mission top-of-mind and making sound engineering decisions to deliver successful outcomes on-time and with high quality. Not only will you build the software, but you&#39;ll also work directly with customers to deploy it. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Emphasis on building, being customer focused, high ownership, and a growth mindset:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain intuitive and easy-to-use User Interfaces for the command and control of cyber assets, the planning of offensive Cyber missions, and remote asset management in far edge environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with users, product designers, and other engineering teams to shape and build User Interfaces that optimize for the delivery of value to the end user.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fetch and manage large streams of data while maintaining performant rendering in a low-friction user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, test, deploy, and demonstrate mission critical code in a tight feedback loop with end users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel up to 25% of the time to participate in customer events and deploy capabilities in the real world.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute back to the development of User Interfaces across all of Anduril, with the aim of developing components that are re-usable across multiple product lines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience using frontend languages such as JavaScript, TypeScript, and React.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to rapidly adapt and perform as a generalist when needed to meet the customer’s mission.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience translating Figma designs into functional code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer-focused mindset with an emphasis on creating intuitive and easy-to-use products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and collaboration skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently possesses and is able to maintain an active U.S. Top Secret security clearance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;US Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$129,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$171,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The salary range for this role is an estimate based on a wide range of compensation factors, inclusive of base salary only. Actual salary offer may vary based on (but not limited to) work experience, education and/or training, critical skills, and/or business considerations. Highly competitive equity grants are included in the majority of full time offers; and are considered part of Anduril&#39;s total compensation package. Additionally, Anduril offers top-tier benefits for full-time employees, including:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
