&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Anduril Industries is a defense technology company with a mission to transform U.S. and allied military capabilities with advanced technology. By bringing the expertise, technology, and business model of the 21st century’s most innovative companies to the defense industry, Anduril is changing how military systems are designed, built and sold. Anduril’s family of systems is powered by Lattice OS, an AI-powered operating system that turns thousands of data streams into a realtime, 3D command and control center. As the world enters an era of strategic competition, Anduril is committed to bringing cutting-edge autonomy, AI, computer vision, sensor fusion, and networking technology to the military in months, not years.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&quot;QualityEngineerIIBattlespace-ABOUTTHETEAM:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Quality Engineering team is a dedicated group of professionals committed to ensuring the highest standards of quality in our processes. We play a crucial role in maintaining the integrity and reliability of our products, working collaboratively to identify, analyze, and resolve quality issues. Our team thrives on a culture of continuous improvement and innovation, leveraging data-driven insights to enhance processes and outcomes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;QualityEngineerIIBattlespace-ABOUTTHEJOB:(thisneedstobeedit)&quot;&gt;ABOUT THE JOB&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;AnswerParser_TextContainer__z_Iiv&quot;&gt;We are seeking a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Quality Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to join our growing team in&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Fort Collins, CO&lt;/strong&gt;. You will work inside and outside the organization to define, develop, and execute processes to ensure the delivery of high quality, reliable and performant radar products to end customers. &amp;nbsp;You will help drive Anduril&#39;s internal quality management system to meet AS9100 requirements. &amp;nbsp;You will partner across the product development organization, production organization, and field operations organizations to continuously improve product quality at the various lifecycle phases of the product through the use of root cause analyses, corrective actions, and failure analyses. &amp;nbsp;This role will be dynamic and full of new engagement, challenges and opportunities. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;AnswerParser_TextContainer__z_Iiv&quot;&gt;If you are someone who has passion for the quality of their work, enjoys hands-on engagement with design engineering, production and vendors, possesses strong analytical skills and attention to detail, then this opportunity is for you! Your proactive problem-solving approach will be vital to our quality initiatives.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;AnswerParser_TextContainer__z_Iiv&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;WHAT YOU’LL DO&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;5641b19f-b299-4b8e-b5f4-aa09600e55d6&quot;&gt;Own Calibration procedure and calibration of production assets along with dev. assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;c82e007e-f52a-43da-bcb3-d8f8141649c7&quot;&gt;Own 6S for the production and development areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;be91060e-301e-4651-8519-a25c0fdb9e0c&quot;&gt;Reviewing Engineering drawings, manufacturing and inspection work instructions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;4ca72bcd-a1f6-40cd-8ffc-36b6999c9eab&quot;&gt;Verifying and inspecting incoming inspection of PCBAs, COTS and mechanical components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;4f886e23-d4b5-46d6-a8a3-bcc97bd8b0a1&quot;&gt;Ensuring non-conformance&#39;s and RCCA&#39;s are accurately controlled, documented and dispositioned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;03c5d2f1-3a8d-4add-9e12-fae95c0fa6c3&quot;&gt;Maintain quality records and support QMS requirements IAW AS9100&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;7b02e8e7-e555-4df5-8763-16f89859bb96&quot;&gt;Trending Quality metrics and performing/leading root cause analysis and corrective action&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;7013238e-e1ba-42cd-992a-0d851cbd2a89&quot;&gt;Review PCB/PCBA schematics, layouts, assembly drawings, and create test documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;AnswerParser_TextContainer__z_Iiv&quot;&gt;REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;599e2df7-ffe6-4be5-925c-cddaa62bbec2&quot;&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering or similar technical field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;0e6adea3-6533-450d-a634-a9fdb1b6f457&quot;&gt;2+ years of experience with PCBAs, electrical assemblies, or electronics manufacturing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;a82f803f-f010-4c81-9f24-0be35afabc1c&quot;&gt;Experience working in AS9100 environment (Preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;c23bafa5-f1f5-456e-b1ed-bae4713dea7c&quot;&gt;Ability to interpret PCB schematics, layouts, and BOMs along with Mechanical components drawings and BOMs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;4347c81f-7dcc-44cb-892c-6bbb371c4047&quot;&gt;Familiarity with PCBA manufacturing processes and component-level troubleshooting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;e69b2340-72bd-45c2-ad19-f2c5583284af&quot;&gt;Hands-on experience with test equipment (multimeter, oscilloscope, power supplies)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be a U.S. Person due to required access to U.S. export controlled information or facilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;a1819abc-a1ec-4cc8-b237-1d4c4abafbc6&quot;&gt;Working knowledge of product development methodologies such as Failure Modes and Effects Analysis (FMEA), Change Management, and Advanced Product Quality Planning (APQP) and Geometric Dimensioning and Tolerancing (GD&amp;amp;T)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;a55b3b8d-bbe6-4b0f-b0a8-699afe4d1653&quot;&gt;Working knowledge of electro-mechanical design and relevant manufacturing processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;dd5da34d-58d7-4c60-8f2f-5a7ace0773d7&quot;&gt;Knowledge of ISO 9001 or AS9100 standard.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-uuid=&quot;8ba8f1da-eb7f-4f13-9aa8-bf7aa4a93517&quot;&gt;Familiarity with IPC-A-600 &amp;amp; IPC-A-610 or standards is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
